# Layer: app

## Structure per domain

- `actions/` — action types + **handlers** (exhaustive switch → controller only)
- `components/` — React UI; enqueue UI actions only
- `viewmodel/` — exposes state via `useContextSelector`; uses validations for guards

## Actions

- Naming: `<CONTROL>_<ACTION>` (e.g. `THEME_DETAILS_SAVE_BUTTON_ON_CLICK`).
- **One** action per user interaction; only UI-derived or identity fields in payload (not state-derived).
- **Handlers**: route to **controller** only; no business logic (trivial routing OK).

## Good / bad

```ts
// BAD — handler mutates or implements rules
case X: setState(...); break;

// GOOD
case X: container.resolve(FooController).run(action); break;
```
